04/08/2010
ATHENS, Greece -- The government announced on Tuesday (August 3rd) the appointment of former Italian Finance Minister Tommaso Padoa-Schioppa as adviser to Prime Minister George Papandreou on economic matters. 
Padoa-Schioppa was chosen due to his substantial knowledge and experience in planning economic policies, the government said. 
He was finance minister of Italy from 2006 to 2008 and has headed the IMF Ministerial Committee. 
The announcement came as a mission of the EU, ECB and IMF is wrapping up an inspection in Athens ahead of another tranche of the 110b-euro aid package aimed at helping the country overcome its debt crisis. 
(ANA-MPA, Businessweek, Xinhua - 03/08/10)
